{
  "stem": "12494.2",
  "chunk_idx": 10,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "And a ghetto house would be a house in the middle of many other houses, which were not ghetto houses.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "The ghetto house would house exclusively Jews, and all the Jews from the non-ghetto houses had to move out.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "Now, what would be reasonably typical would be that a ghetto house, particularly in the non-Jewish areas of town, the mixed areas of town-- would be surrounded by five or six non-ghetto houses.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "The ghetto houses, of course, represented a hardship for both parts, the Jewish and the non-Jewish part.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "If a house was declared a ghetto house, then the non-Jews had to move out, and the-- I forgot what they were given, about a week-- and move elsewhere, usually in abandoned Jewish apartments elsewhere in town.",
      "word_count": 37
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And most of them did well, they got a better apartment than they had before, a better flat than they had before.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And the Jews in turn had to move into the ghetto houses, and that was a high-density type situation.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Generally it was expected there would be three or four people per room in the-- in the ghetto houses.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was-- I was-- but I really sought an assignment to become the guy who would arrange things in our district.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "So I-- I was assigned to be-- to head that district, and I designated the house in which we had our flat as a ghetto house, so that our non-Jewish neighbors had to move out.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And in turn, most members of our family, who-- who had to move out of what became non-ghetto houses, moved in with us.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And that took up-- that process took up probably the first three weeks of June.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And then very soon our transport, the Kasztner transport left on June 30.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
